The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Lucknow, Aug. 24 (PTI): Spencers outlets did brisk business today, a day after they were ordered to shut down along with Reliance Fresh stores.

 The closure was ordered after Reliance outlets were ransacked by traders protesting against retail chains. 

 We have not seen an official communique from the state. Our stores were operational yesterday and are so till now, RPG vice-chairman Sanjiv Goenka said.

 ow district magistrate Chandra Bhanu said the order did not apply to Spencers as there was no law-and-order problem with its stores. 

 Officials also clarified that the closure order was limited to Lucknow and Varanasi. 

 Bangalore (PTI): An 11-year-old girl was beaten up by teachers for not doing her homework properly, police said. A case of assault, molestation and use of abusive words has been filed against the school. 

 Chennai: The armys lady cadets will get equal training time as the gentlemen from the next April. Their training course will be for 49 weeks like that of gentleman cadets. Women get only 26 weeks now.

 Cuttack: Orissa director-general of police (homeguards) B.B. Mohanti, who has been allegedly shielding his son since he jumped parole last year in a rape case, was suspended on Friday. 

 Cuttack: The Orissa consumer disputes redressal commission has imposed a fine of Rs 1 lakh, in addition to compensation, on Indian for failing to safeguard the baggage of a passenger. The luggage had gone missing before the Indian flight reached Singapore on July 6, 1999. The airline has been asked to pay the amount by October 31.

 Chennai (PTI): Madras High Court has dismissed a PIL filed against music director A.R. Rahman and Bharti Enterprises chairman Sunil Mittal, accusing them of showing disrespect to the national anthem in a recent composition.




